{"id": 231290188, "title": "Michael Mosley search teams pictured battling 'stifling' heat in hunt for missing TV doctor", "text": "Search efforts continue in the hunt for missing TV doctor Michael Mosley. Police and firefighters have been using drones to scour the Greek island of Symi in a bid to find the 67-year-old, who vanished on Wednesday, June 5. The father-of-four was last seen by CCTV at a grey-stoned house beside a harbour. Officials believe he may have walked along a steep uphill concrete road, which has a small path at the end, leading into a rocky landscape with little vegetation beyond thistles and dry grass. Red Cross teams were among those braving the stifling heat to search for Dr Mosley in the mountains on Saturday, June 8. Firefighters have had to split up to search multiple summits alone as it was too dangerous for large crews to tackle. READ MORE: Search for missing Dr Michael Mosley continues as his wife says 'we will not lose hope' - updates Dr Mosley's wife, Clare, who raised the alarm about his disappearance, said the family were \"incredibly grateful\" to those \"working tirelessly to help find Michael\". She said the days since he vanished had been the \"longest and most unbearable\" but vowed: \"We will not lose hope.\" For the latest news on Dr Mosley's disappearance, follow our live blog. The latest updates will be added as and when we get them.", "summary": "The popular broadcaster went missing on the Greek island of Symi during a holiday after telling his wife he was taking a walk", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/showbiz-tv/gallery/michael-mosley-search-teams-pictured-29318376", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/incoming/article29318387.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Michael-Mosley-missing.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 14:52:02", "author": "Kelly Ashmore", "authors": ["Kelly Ashmore"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.032}